# .graphifyignore.example — per-project ignore template.
#
# YOU PROBABLY DON'T NEED THIS. Media (img/video/audio/pdf/office) is already
# excluded in EVERY project by the GLOBAL ignore (~/.graphify/graphifyignore +
# patch-global-ignore.py). Secrets/.env are skipped built-in everywhere.
#
# Use a per-project .graphifyignore ONLY for project-specific excludes the global
# layer and .gitignore don't already cover.
#
# ⚠️ FOOTGUN (verified): a .graphifyignore in a directory makes graphify STOP
# reading that directory's .gitignore (it does NOT merge — last-match-wins per
# file, but .gitignore is shadowed entirely when .graphifyignore exists in the
# same dir). So if you add one, COPY OVER any non-secret .gitignore rules you
# still need (build dirs, data dumps, etc.). Secrets stay safe regardless (built-in).
#
# gitignore syntax: glob patterns, last-match-wins, `!` re-includes.

# example: carry over the project's own .gitignore rules that aren't secrets
# (secrets like .env are already handled built-in, no need to list them):
# build/
# dist/
# node_modules/
# db-backups/

# example: project-specific extra excludes
# vendor/
# *.generated.ts
